    <items>
        <item id="i63929e75e9b46174553720433c5e3bbc1e">
            <label key="d2b5831ed246ec12665b138b97eb36b5">
                <text>The diagram on the right shows one process that causes cities to sink.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="4ade6a07d44d7151565006de94e2714f">
                <text>Which one of the following sentences best explains how cities sink by this process?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="c82e24677ef30b1d7b35203159fda79f">
                <text>Water is removed from the sand layer, forcing sand into the clay layer.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="9603a0a83efaba1aaf0b4b16e8a36267">
                <text>Water is removed from the clay layer, forcing clay into the sand layer.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="97c4f1fd538d3d8416a8f76edd122d67">
                <text>Water moves from the sand layer into the clay layer, causing the sand layer to compact.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="ced0f6d61945683154b361eb3c773c1d">
                <text>Water moves from the clay layer into the sand layer, causing the clay layer to compact. </text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i63929e97a6e16175052131484edd5b98b1">
            <label key="db955e41785d87c166b01498964e6b26">
                <text>A news article claims, ‘Land subsidence is a serious issue that affects <strong>only</strong> Asian tropical cities’. </text>
            </label>
            <label key="e3bf924a05642700f1a803b35d31a84f">
                <text>An editor uses the table on the right to fact-check the article.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="70e556e23c83f135d053a33ec894200b">
                <text>The editor decides the claim is false.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="69766e3f918cc695d4d5bf731c3cdad9">
                <text>Which of the following statements support the editor’s decision?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="89b1c1de80f35eb0f385836481797561">
                <text>Select all correct answers.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="e7bbd75cf2dc892abefcffc3889c3bbb">
                <text>Cities that are most affected by land subsidence are in Asia.  </text>
            </label>
            <label key="cdc12de1e89e66121c2443f18d8aacd6">
                <text>Tokyo, Tianjin and New York are affected by land subsidence.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="57e2706a0e26ecadcd9246b1e90b77f0">
                <text>London and Barcelona are sinking at a rate of 15 mm/year.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="645eb1e71e504f0a3d5f3d2e0855ad80">
                <text>Ho Chi Minh City has been sinking at a rate of 80 mm/year over the last 20 years. </text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i63929eb35208523322c654befc919bd2c">
            <label key="a80413ab352dda52fd0af7fe5b6e9b5e">
                <text>Causes of land subsidence include the removal of ground water, the extraction of oil and gas, and the weight of buildings.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="ad29b2a880f26b349034beefb23bf620">
                <text>Which of these additional factors could also cause land subsidence?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="89b1c1de80f35eb0f385836481797561">
                <text>Select all correct answers.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="903a27988610264db7bb749fb5b3e218">
                <text>crop irrigation using rainwater stored in tanks</text>
            </label>
            <label key="dd0e2bcf2acd6b6afd6fed1529c96da9">
                <text>melting of glaciers</text>
            </label>
            <label key="2da8fe1e938432cfed1a686cecdb57b1">
                <text>movement of tectonic plates</text>
            </label>
            <label key="8926c466fae77198cf3bc79d04da8fc1">
                <text>seasonal changes of water flow in rivers</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i63bb5d5a0ef3623216846038fab25e5283">
            <label key="0012209c08c7c463d613b3cd582db523">
                <text>Carbon capture, a method for removing excess carbon dioxide (CO₂) from the atmosphere, could also help reduce land subsidence.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="75bb8c94e4d7ff629117033e345a4b7c">
                <text>Carbon capture involves injecting CO₂ into porous rock from which oil has been extracted.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="675e6465f7d904e90aeaea4f1366aab0">
                <text>Policymakers require trustworthy information to decide what action is needed to reduce the amount of CO₂ in the atmosphere and to reduce land subsidence.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="6b4324524f6cbeb75f71c45d25007f88">
                <text>Which one of the following sources of information about carbon capture is <strong>most</strong> trustworthy?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="8295d30429b9238dce40a8caea2323bd">
                <text>a competition on social media to find the best carbon capture technology</text>
            </label>
            <label key="0fc4dba963f3d40369099a02965714e6">
                <text>an opinion piece in <em>Sustainable Earthlovers</em> magazine featuring a debate between science journalists</text>
            </label>
            <label key="1e638b1eb5afc12fa509b53f92c78a73">
                <text>an editorial in the <em>Magson State Bank Report</em> discussing carbon capture and the likelihood of CO₂ remaining underground</text>
            </label>
            <label key="11bd84bddd978abfad80eeebbbf7222e">
                <text>an article in the peer-reviewed journal <em>Science of Carbon Journal</em> about energy costs associated with carbon capture</text>
            </label>
            <label key="14a742a5c8a85e7bdbb23e8e791c910b">
                <text>Explain your choice.</text>
            </label>
        </item>
    </items>
